{
  "stem": "22979.2",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But the guard, the Hlinka Guard, promised-- told us-- promised us-- that we are taken to work, to Germany so we can help our families who are behind and support them.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So it was not [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Since we were young-- so we said, oh, that'd be wonderful, because you know, it was horrible already-- no money, no food.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we went.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But, you know, leaving your home-- home base-- home city-- is very hard.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So that was the last time I saw my parents.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was March 24, 1942.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And we traveled overnight to this camp where they concentrated the girls.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They needed 1,000.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And from the whole-- from the cities which surrounded us, from Presov, Kosice, Bardejov and so, they brought in with trucks to this-- to this city, the girls.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And March 26, we had to line up, 5 in rows, and march very early in the morning-- so the rest of the population wouldn't see us-- to the railroad station.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And far away, we saw already a long track of cattle cars.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We didn't even think of it that those are suited for us-- [LAUGHS] --for we are human beings.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But what a disappointment.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We came there, and the guards started screaming.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "The cattle cars opened.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "In Slovakian, actually, up, up, you-- you dirty Jewish whores, and so on.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So they pushed about 60 to 80 of us in one cattle car.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In the center of the cattle car were two buckets of water.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "One-- no-- one was full of water, and the other was empty.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They locked the cattle car, and there we went-- unknown where.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We thought we are traveling to Germany for work, but what a disappointment.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
